                  Isaac 
                  Harrison
               <interp inst="t18141026-25-person294" type="surname" value="Harrison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18141026-25-person294" type="given" value="Isaac"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18141026-25-person294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Our warehouse is some distance from the gateway where this package was. This package I had just received; these hats were in our own private gateway.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I am as innocent of this charge as the child unborn. I have served in the army eighteen years. I have been transported before for seven years for a crime that I was guilty of. I applied to the society for the refuge of the destitute; it was too full to admit me. They furnished me with one pound; I went into the city; I was taken up by a police officer; it was impossible for me to get any employ, as my character was gone. Should I unfortunately be found guilty, I hope to be sent out of this country for ever, as I am certain I could not get my living in this country.</p>
